<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,517,258,285]" pageId="2">Note on the genus spelling.</emphasis>
In the original publication, 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[829,998,259,285]" pageId="2" pagination="4 - 5" refId="ref7023" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1913) Die Familie der Gonyleptiden der Opiliones-Laniatores. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (4 - 5), 1 - 472, Pl. Ia, b." type="journal article" year="1913">Roewer (1913)</bibRefCitation>
consistently spelled the genus name as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[151,330,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthpachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,330,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthpachylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<collectingCountry box="[343,385,295,321]" name="New Zealand" pageId="2">NZ</collectingCountry>
, 1: 22]; 10 years later he emended it by inserting a missing 
<emphasis box="[1048,1092,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2">“o”</emphasis>
, to get the current spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Roewer" authorityYear="1923" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthopachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthopachylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[437,604,331,357]" pageId="2" refId="ref7061" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1923) Die Weberknechte der Erde. Systematische Bearbeitung der bisher bekannten Opiliones. G. Fischer Verlag, Jena, 1116 pp." type="book" year="1923">Roewer (1923)</bibRefCitation>
does not explain the reasons for the change, according to ICZN Art. 33.2.1. this action is clearly intentional (
<emphasis box="[521,556,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2">i.e.</emphasis>
, the original and the modified spellings are both cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[1207,1361,367,393]" pageId="2" refId="ref7061" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1923) Die Weberknechte der Erde. Systematische Bearbeitung der bisher bekannten Opiliones. G. Fischer Verlag, Jena, 1116 pp." type="book" year="1923">Roewer 1923</bibRefCitation>
), what constitutes primarily an unjustified emendation [
<emphasis box="[691,719,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2">cf.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[724,764,403,429]" name="New Zealand" pageId="2">NZ</collectingCountry>
, 1: 17]. Moreover, the original spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[1203,1382,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthpachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1203,1382,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthpachylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be interpreted as an inadvertent error, since this category is not met by the incorrect use of connecting vowels in forming a name (ICZN, Art. 32.5.1.). In any case, the emended spelling 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Roewer" authorityYear="1923" box="[968,1161,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthopachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1161,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthopachylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gained prevailing usage (
<emphasis box="[161,189,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="2">cf.</emphasis>
synonymy in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kury, A. B." box="[346,470,511,537]" pageId="2" pagination="5 - 337" refId="ref6264" refString="Kury, A. B. (2003) Annotated catalogue of the Laniatores of the New World (Arachnida, Opiliones). Revista Iberica de Aracnologia, Volumen especial monografico, 1, 5 - 337." type="journal article" year="2003">Kury 2003</bibRefCitation>
), so it became by force of use a “justified emendation” (ICZN Art. 33.2.3.1.), 
<emphasis box="[1339,1373,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2">i.e.</emphasis>
, with no separate authorship and date, rendering 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1913" box="[632,811,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthpachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,811,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthpachylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the “incorrect original spelling”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,582,608]" pageId="2">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Roewer" authorityYear="1923" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[359,666,583,609]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthopachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">
<emphasis box="[359,666,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthopachylus aculeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. has been deemed to be one of the most widespread harvestmen in South America. It was cited from Cayenne in the 
<collectingCountry box="[745,911,619,645]" name="French Guiana" pageId="2">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
(presumed “ 
<typeStatus box="[1056,1120,619,645]" pageId="2">types</typeStatus>
” of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[1169,1429,619,645]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Gonyleptes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acanthurus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1429,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="2">Gonyleptes acanthurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." box="[295,501,655,681]" pageId="2" refId="ref7061" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1923) Die Weberknechte der Erde. Systematische Bearbeitung der bisher bekannten Opiliones. G. Fischer Verlag, Jena, 1116 pp." type="book" year="1923">Roewer 1923: 413</bibRefCitation>
) up to the Strait of Magellan, in the southernmost tip of the continent (
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer, C. F." pageId="2" pagination="179 - 284" refId="ref7092" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1929) Weitere Weberknechte III. III. Erganzung der &quot; Weberknechte der Erde &quot;, 1923. Abhandlungen herausgegeben vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen, 27 (2), 179 - 284, pl. I." type="journal article" year="1929">Roewer 1929: 190</bibRefCitation>
, 
<specimenCount box="[206,333,691,718]" pageId="2" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao, C. de" box="[351,579,691,717]" pageId="2" pagination="601 - 630" refId="ref6522" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. de (1939) Les arachnides et la zoogeographie de l'Argentine. Physis, 17 (49), 601 - 630." type="journal article" year="1939">Mello-Leitão (1939)</bibRefCitation>
argued that the species spreads over “toute l’Amérique du Sud, du coté atlantique”, an exaggerated assertion repeated by B. Soares &amp; H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soares, B. A. M. &amp; Soares, H. E. M." box="[834,994,726,753]" pageId="2" pagination="225 - 302" refId="ref7174" refString="Soares, B. A. M. &amp; Soares, H. E. M. (1954) Monografia dos generos de opilioes neotropicos III. Arquivos de Zoologia do Estado de Sao Paulo, 8 (9), 225 - 302." type="journal article" year="1954">Soares (1954)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Eisner, T. &amp; Rossini, C. &amp; Gonzalez, A. &amp; Eisner, M." box="[1006,1226,727,753]" pageId="2" pagination="1313 - 1321" refId="ref5928" refString="Eisner, T., Rossini, C., Gonzalez, A. &amp; Eisner, M. (2004) Chemical defense of an opilionid (Acanthopachylus aculeatus). The Journal of Experimental Biology, 207, 1313 - 1321. https: // doi. org / 10.1242 / jeb. 00849" type="journal article" year="2004">
Eisner 
<emphasis box="[1085,1141,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
, citing 
<bibRefCitation author="Capocasale, R. &amp; Bruno Trezza, L." pageId="2" pagination="19 - 32" refId="ref5751" refString="Capocasale, R. &amp; Bruno Trezza, L. (1964) Biologia de Acanthopachylus aculeatus (Kirby, 1819), (Opiliones; Pachylinae). Revista de la Sociedad Uruguaya de Entomologia, 6, 19 - 32." type="journal article" year="1964">Capocasale &amp; Bruno Trezza (1964)</bibRefCitation>
, still claimed that the species extends from the Guianas to 
<collectingCountry box="[1082,1197,763,789]" name="Argentina" pageId="2">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. The only well documented records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Roewer" authorityYear="1923" box="[361,554,799,825]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Acanthopachylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[361,554,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="2">Acanthopachylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, come from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[910,978,799,825]" name="Brazil" pageId="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[993,1271,799,825]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="2">Rio Grande do Sul State</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1291,1389,799,825]" name="Uruguay" pageId="2">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,262,835,861]" name="Argentina" pageId="2">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ringuelet, R. A." box="[276,453,834,861]" pageId="2" pagination="127 - 439" refId="ref6977" refString="Ringuelet, R. A. (1959) Los aracnidos argentinos del orden Opiliones. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia, Cs. Zool., 5 (2), 127 - 439, pls. I - XX." type="journal article" year="1959">Ringuelet 1959</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Capocasale, R." box="[464,657,835,861]" pageId="2" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref5718" refString="Capocasale, R. (1968) Nuevos aportes para el conocimiento de la distribucion geografica de los opiliones de Uruguay. Neotropica, 14 (44), 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="1968">Capocasale 1968</bibRefCitation>
; H. Soares &amp; B. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soares, H. E. M. &amp; Soares, B. A. M." box="[843,983,835,861]" pageId="2" pagination="87 - 100" refId="ref7220" refString="Soares, H. E. M. &amp; Soares, B. A. M. (1986) Opera opiliologica varia. XXVI. (Opiliones, Gonyleptidae). Revista brasileira de Entomologia, 30 (1), 87 - 100." type="journal article" year="1986">Soares 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kury, A. B." box="[994,1119,835,861]" pageId="2" pagination="5 - 337" refId="ref6264" refString="Kury, A. B. (2003) Annotated catalogue of the Laniatores of the New World (Arachnida, Opiliones). Revista Iberica de Aracnologia, Volumen especial monografico, 1, 5 - 337." type="journal article" year="2003">Kury 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Despite this restriction, the genus distributes over an extensive range on grassland-type biomes (Pampas in 
<collectingCountry box="[1036,1150,871,897]" name="Argentina" pageId="2">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, similar savanna environments in 
<collectingCountry box="[253,351,907,933]" name="Uruguay" pageId="2">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[404,476,907,933]" name="Brazil" pageId="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Acosta, L. E." box="[485,630,907,933]" pageId="2" pagination="69 - 84" refId="ref5341" refString="Acosta, L. E. (2002) Patrones zoogeograficos de los opiliones argentinos (Arachnida: Opiliones). Revista Iberica de Aracnologia, 6, 69 - 84." type="journal article" year="2002">Acosta 2002</bibRefCitation>
), along with some peripheral records in neighboring ecoregions (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1422,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1232,1256]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,152,1209]" captionTargetId="figure-366@6.[151,1436,151,1209]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution of Acanthopachylus aculeatus (Kirby) (blue dots) and A. robustus (Holmberg) comb. nov. (red dots) in Argentina, Uruguay and southern Brazil. Records with verified taxonomic identity are denoted with full color symbols, small white dots represent literature citations not checked as yet. Ecoregions according to Olson et al. (2001); both grassland-type ecoregions (Humid Pampas on the Argentinean side, Uruguayan Savanna in Uruguay and southern Brazil) are given the same color (light yellow). APAF: Alto Parana Atlantic Forests; HCH: Humid Chaco; MS: Southern Cone Mesopotamian Savanna; ESP: Espinal. Inset (bottom right): location of the area represented in South America." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531544/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Both species have marked synantropic habits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
